The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs, specifically parameterized algorithms. The focus is on graphs of polynomial growth, which suggests that the paper may belong to categories related to graph theory and combinatorics. The use of treewidth and dynamic programming techniques further supports this. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely categories for this paper.
